headline: EXPE Q2 Deep Dive: B2B and International Growth Offset U.S. Travel Softness
summary: Online travel agency Expedia (NASDAQ:EXPE) reported Q2 CY2025 results beating Wall Street’s revenue expectations, with sales up 6.4% year on year to $3.79 billion. Its non-GAAP profit of $4.24 per share was 2.7% above analysts’ consensus estimates.
